FBIS4-27334 "dreas105__a94015" FBIS-EAS-94-105-A Daily Report 30 May 1994 ANNEX Japan LDP's Kono Asks Hata To Resign Before Summit LDP's Kono Asks Hata To Resign Before Summit OW3105051094 Tokyo NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN in Japanese 30 May 94 Morning Edition p 2 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY OW3105051094 Tokyo NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN Japanese BFN [Text] Yohei Kono, president of the Liberal Democratic Party [LDP], gave a speech in Niigata City on 29 May, in which he said, "What can (Prime Minister Tsutomu Hata's) minority government promise when it goes to the meeting of leaders of the advanced nations (the Naples Summit)? If something is agreed upon at the summit, will it be able to implement it? We have to think about whom we should send out as a responsible representative to the international community." He indicated that the Hata cabinet should resign before the summit is held on 8 July.
